init_text:
Are We Being Bad Citizens If We Don't Keep Up With the News?

In your opinion, are we being bad citizens if we don't keep up with the news? Do you think all people have some responsibility to know what is going on in the world? Does engaging with current events actually do anything at all? Why do you think the way you do?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I believe that all people should be knowledgeable in their country and community.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So I believe that we are bad citizens if we do not keep up with what is going on in the world.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And we should not tolerate that in a functioning democratic society.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: In addition, we should be part of a society that is active and makes its voice heard on political issues to get them addressed properly.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Democracy is not just about elections; it is about being aware, participating in discourse, and holding our leaders accountable for their actions or in actions that they

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: as we are not fulfilling our duty as citizens.
